Eventually, law catches up with The Wire which published a misleading and defamatory story against Jay Shah. Now, the editor and writer of The Wire will get the taste of their own medicine. #LiarWireNailed

Gujarat High Court’s verdict clearly indicates that the article published on web portal ‘The Wire’ is defamatory and deserves a detailed trial.  The Wire will now face the music, pushing them to the brink of bankruptcy. #LiarWireNailed
Hon’ble Gujarat HC was prima facie satisfied that the article published by web news portal is defamatory and now #LiarWireNailed will have to face criminal trial.
Hon’ble Gujarat HC rejected the plea seeking quashing of the complaint by Wire and author of article and editors including others,  holding that there is prima facie case against the #LiarWireNailed.
The Advocate of the accused, the author and editors of “The Wire”, objected to disposing the case as suggested by the Gujarat HC for completing the trial within 6 months. #LiarWireNailed

The rejection of the petition by the Gujarat HC can be seen as prima facie conclusion with regard to defamation by the editors and more particularly the author of the article, who are accused. #LiarWireNailed

The complainant had alleged malice and malafide intention against the accused, which after examination, appears to be prima facie accepted by the Hon’ble HC. This can be seen as huge blow to #LiarWireNailed.
Gujarat HC finds merit in Jay Shah's defamation case against the Wire, rejecting Wire's petition to quash the case. The Wire's woes have just began. #LiarWireNailed
Huge setback for The Wire as Siddharth Varadarajan and Mangalam Kesavan Venu will have to face Criminal Trial in Jay Shah case. #LiarWireNailed
The Wire's plea is turned down by the High Court and Siddharth Varadarajan and Mangalam Kesavan Venu along with others will have to face trial in Jay Shah's defamation case. #LiarWireNailed
Gujarat HC found substance in the complaint and refused to interfere in Jay Shah's defamation case against The Wire. #LiarWireNailed
